<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2020-03-21</DATELINE><TITLE>The index case of SARS-CoV-2 in Scotland</TITLE><BODY>Summary Since its identification in December 2019, SARS-CoV-2 has infected 125,048 persons globally with cases identified in 118 countries across all continents. We report on the Scottish index case of SARS-CoV-2 infection, the virus causing COVID-19.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>